{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blog/pointillism","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Pointillstic lines</h1>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d8b187c11965c00fb0d2fc7e1f819a51/3fb84/panda.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Plotting result\"\n        title=\"Plotting result\"\n        src=\"/static/d8b187c11965c00fb0d2fc7e1f819a51/4b190/panda.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d8b187c11965c00fb0d2fc7e1f819a51/e07e9/panda.jpg 200w,\n/static/d8b187c11965c00fb0d2fc7e1f819a51/066f9/panda.jpg 400w,\n/static/d8b187c11965c00fb0d2fc7e1f819a51/4b190/panda.jpg 800w,\n/static/d8b187c11965c00fb0d2fc7e1f819a51/e5166/panda.jpg 1200w,\n/static/d8b187c11965c00fb0d2fc7e1f819a51/b17f8/panda.jpg 1600w,\n/static/d8b187c11965c00fb0d2fc7e1f819a51/3fb84/panda.jpg 2835w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>This is a follow up from my pointillism exploration with plotterbjork. I wasn't too happy with the pointillism, since drawing mere points didn't really differ from just using a poor inkjet printer. So this uses a very similar idea, but instead of points it draws lines! And the results look <strong>great</strong>.</p>\n<p>It's evident from afar and even more so close up that this is something a little different than just a printer. The lines have a varying thickness due to how the ink flows, and each start and end point has a bit of a point on it. The lines are biased towards drawing upwards vertically, which gives the Panda a nice hairy look!</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b59600069f7b147fc5f4abc4817dba49/9568a/panda_closeup.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Close up of the result\"\n        title=\"Close up of the result\"\n        src=\"/static/b59600069f7b147fc5f4abc4817dba49/4b190/panda_closeup.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b59600069f7b147fc5f4abc4817dba49/e07e9/panda_closeup.jpg 200w,\n/static/b59600069f7b147fc5f4abc4817dba49/066f9/panda_closeup.jpg 400w,\n/static/b59600069f7b147fc5f4abc4817dba49/4b190/panda_closeup.jpg 800w,\n/static/b59600069f7b147fc5f4abc4817dba49/e5166/panda_closeup.jpg 1200w,\n/static/b59600069f7b147fc5f4abc4817dba49/b17f8/panda_closeup.jpg 1600w,\n/static/b59600069f7b147fc5f4abc4817dba49/9568a/panda_closeup.jpg 3024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>After the panda came out looking fabulous I went ahead and plotted some other\nblack and white animals:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bc519f4d31cddd4fc4c164220b499af5/9568a/orca.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Orca\"\n        title=\"Orca\"\n        src=\"/static/bc519f4d31cddd4fc4c164220b499af5/4b190/orca.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bc519f4d31cddd4fc4c164220b499af5/e07e9/orca.jpg 200w,\n/static/bc519f4d31cddd4fc4c164220b499af5/066f9/orca.jpg 400w,\n/static/bc519f4d31cddd4fc4c164220b499af5/4b190/orca.jpg 800w,\n/static/bc519f4d31cddd4fc4c164220b499af5/e5166/orca.jpg 1200w,\n/static/bc519f4d31cddd4fc4c164220b499af5/b17f8/orca.jpg 1600w,\n/static/bc519f4d31cddd4fc4c164220b499af5/9568a/orca.jpg 3024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Code modified to bias the lines from left to right, to sell the illusion of movement, and give the orca a <em>slick</em> look.</p>\n<p>Full code below without the setup() and helper functions for drawing lines etc.\nI've abstracted those out to a different file, so will not be including them each time.</p>\n<p>Full code for the sketch:</p>\n<pre><code>PImage img;\nint imageX, imageY, imageW, imageH;\nint x, y, i=0;\nint lastX = x;\nint lastY = y;\nint direction = 1;\nboolean done = false;\nint delay = 250;\n\nvoid draw() {\n  frameRate(99999);\n  int imageCutoff = 1183; // Vertical point to cut the image at. Gotten by printing imageY values while seeing how it's drawn\n\n  if (i == 0) {\n    x = VERTICAL_CENTER;\n    y = HORIZONTAL_CENTER;\n    img = loadImage(\"orca1.jpg\");\n    imageMode(CENTER);\n    imageW = img.width;\n    imageH = img.height;\n    imageX = 0;\n    imageY = 0;\n  }\n\n  imageX = i * (int) random(15,60);\n\n  if (imageX > imageW) {\n    imageX = 0;\n    imageY = imageY + 1;\n    i = 1;\n    stroke(0, 0, 200, 90);\n    x = (int) map(imageX, 0, imageW, xMin, xMax);\n    y = (int) map(imageY, 0, imageH, yMin, yMax);\n    direction = -1 * direction;\n  }\n\n  if (imageY > imageH) {\n    println(\"DONE!\");\n    done = true;\n  }\n\n  color pix = img.get(imageX, imageY);\n  int brightness = (int) brightness(pix);\n\n  if (brightness &#x3C; 50 &#x26;&#x26; !done) {\n    x = (int) map(imageX, 0, imageW, xMin, xMax);\n    y = (int) map(imageY, 0, imageH, yMin, yMax);\n    //drawPoint(y + 500, x -500, 0);\n    // drawLine(x + 500, y - 500, (int) random(yMin, yMax), xMax, false, 0); start from bottom?\n    int horizontalOffset = 1000;\n    int verticalOffset = 500;\n    int lineLength = 100;\n    int originY = (int) y + verticalOffset;\n    int originX = (int) x - horizontalOffset;\n    line_clipped(originY, originX, originY + (int) random(10, 20), originX + (int) random(lineLength/2, 2*lineLength), true, delay);\n    //line_clipped(y, x, y + (int) random(-10, 20), x + direction*(int) random(50, 100), true, delay);\n    lastY=y;\n    lastX=x;\n  }\n  i = i+1;\n}\n</code></pre>","frontmatter":{"date":"December 24, 2020","slug":"/blog/pointillism","title":"Pointillism Extended"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/pointillism"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}